{"id":8107490421,"url":"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8334/8107490421_515dd92986.jpg","path":"c3b/4f4/c3b4f47b504f6c74f5d96ddd4aded17.jpg","date":"2012-08-16","year":2012,"month":8,"lon":114.946976,"lat":25.865597,"tags":"ganzhou","S2CellId":"3141000000000000","result":1757,"accuracy":0.24016818,"title":"IMG_4624s","description":"Ganzhou%2C+China.+In+the+picture+is+the+northeastern+corner+of+the+city.+View+from+the+floating+bridge.%0A%3Ca+href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FGanzhou%22+rel%3D%22nofollow%22%3Een.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FGanzhou%3C%2Fa%3E%3A+%0AGanzhou+%28Chinese%3A+%E8%B5%A3%E5%B7%9E%3B+pinyin%3A+G%C3%A0nzh%C5%8Du%29%2C+formerly+romanized+as+Kanchow%2C+is+a+prefecture-level+city.%0AIn+201%2C+Emperor+Gaozu+of+the+Han+Dynasty+established+a+county+in+the+territory+of+modern+Ganzhou.+In+those+early+years%2C+ethnic+Han+settlement+and+authority+in+the+area+was+minimal+and+largely+restricted+to+the+Gan+River+basin.+The+river%2C+a+tributary+of+the+Yangtze+River+via+Poyang+Lake%2C+provided+a+route+of+communication+from+the+north+as+well+as+irrigation+for+rice+farming.%0A%0ADuring+the+Sui+Dynasty+the+county+administration+was+promoted+to+prefecture+status+and+the+area+called+Qianzhou+%28%E8%99%94%E5%B7%9E%29.+During+the+Song+Dynasty+immigration+from+the+north+bolstered+the+local+population+and+drove+local+aboriginal+tribes+further+into+the+hills.+Especially+after+the+fall+of+the+Northern+Song+capital+of+Kaifeng%2C+migrants+increased+dramatically.+The+name+was+officially+changed+to+Ganzhou+in+the+Southern+Song.%0A%0ADuring+the+late+1800s+Ganzhou+was+opened+as+one+of+the+southern+treaty+ports+and+became+a+minor+base+for+foreign+companies.+Between+1929+and+1934%2C+Ganzhou+formed+a+part+of+the+Jiangxi+Soviet%2C+one+of+the+bases+of+the+Communist+Party+of+China.+Due+to+its+proximity+to+the+Red+capital+Ruijin+%28%E7%91%9E%E9%87%91%29%2C+Ganzhou+was+subject+to+a+number+of+Kuomintang+encirclement+campaigns.%0A%0ABetween+1939+and+1945%2C+Chiang+Ching-kuo+was+appointed+by+the+Government+of+the+Republic+of+China+as+commissioner+of+Gannan+Prefecture+%28Chinese%3A+%E8%B4%9B%E5%8D%97%29%2C+then+the+name+of+the+surrounding+regions+of+Ganzhou.+There+he+banned+smoking%2C+gambling+and+prostitution%2C+studied+governmental+management%2C+allowed+for+economic+expansion+and+a+change+in+social+outlook.+His+efforts+were+hailed+as+a+miracle+in+the+political+war+in+China%2C+then+coined+as+the+%22Gannan+New+Deal%22+%28%E8%B4%9B%E5%8D%97%E6%96%B0%E6%94%BF%29.+During+his+time+in+Gannan%2C+from+1940+he+implemented+a+%22public+information+desk%22+where+ordinary+people+could+visit+him+if+they+had+problems%2C+and+according+to+records%2C+Chiang+Ching-kuo+received+a+total+of+1%2C023+people+during+such+sessions+in+1942.+In+regards+to+the+ban+on+prostitution+and+closing+of+brothels%2C+Chiang+implemented+a+policy+where+former+prostitutes+became+employed+in+factories.+Due+to+the+large+number+of+refugees+in+Ganzhou+as+a+result+from+the+ongoing+war%2C+thousands+of+orphans+lived+on+the+street%3B+in+June+1942%2C+Chiang+Ching-kuo+formally+established+the+Chinese+Children%27s+Village+%28%E4%B8%AD%E8%8F%AF%E5%85%92%E7%AB%A5%E6%96%B0%E6%9D%91%29+in+the+outskirts+of+Ganzhou%2C+with+facilities+such+as+a+nursery%2C+kindergarten%2C+primary+school%2C+hospital+and+gymnasium."}
